# Force LF for all text in the repo, on every platform.
#
# Why this matters here specifically: the catalog builder
# (scripts/build-catalog.mjs) hashes each extension's source tree
# byte-for-byte to (a) decide whether to repackage its zip and (b) record
# a `sourceHash` that the version-bump gate (scripts/check-versions.mjs)
# compares against. CI runs on Linux (LF); a Windows checkout with CRLF
# would produce different bytes — different hashes, spurious "source
# changed" reports, and — if a zip were ever cut on Windows — installable
# bundles that differ from the Linux ones for no real reason.
#
# `* text=auto eol=lf` normalises line endings to LF in the working tree
# regardless of core.autocrlf, so every contributor hashes the same bytes
# CI does.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary types that must never be touched (none committed today, but guard
# against future additions so they aren't corrupted by EOL normalisation).
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.gif binary
*.zip binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
